  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Dynamic Elements</h2>
    <p>Elements added to the DOM after page load are automatically observed via a MutationObserver. No manual initialization is needed.</p>

    <code-block language="javascript" show-lines label="Dynamically added ticker elements">{{ dynamicCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The original text content serves as a no-JS fallback</li>
      <li>The semantic <code>&lt;data&gt;</code> element with <code>value</code> attribute provides machine-readable data at all times</li>
      <li><code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> is respected &mdash; no animation when the user requests it</li>
      <li><code>font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums</code> prevents layout shift during animation</li>
      <li>No wrapper element &mdash; the <code>&lt;data&gt;</code> <em>is</em> the enhanced element</li>
      <li>Screen readers see the final value via the <code>value</code> attribute, not the animated intermediate values</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
